# In/Ex

I start with the Gaussian weighted averages over the `11 x 11 x 11 x Ch` cubes at
each synapse location.

Here I re-factor the data into a two-variable dataset: 

INH $:= \text{Z-score} \circ \sum{\text{Inhibitory Features}}$

EX $:= \text{Z-score} \circ \sum{\text{Excitatory Features}}$

Then plot the new dataset colored by the given `gaba` labels.
The ellipses superimposed on the plot correspond to the class conditional covariances (at 1,2, and 3 standard deviations) of
the components.


```{r inex, fig.width = 8, fig.height = 8, echo = FALSE}
ndat <- data.frame(
                   "inhibitory" = Reduce('+', sdat[, ccol == 'green']), 
                   "excitatory" = Reduce('+', sdat[, ccol == 'red'])
                   )

sndat <- data.frame(gaba = gaba, scale(ndat, center = TRUE, scale = TRUE))

plot(sndat[, -1], type = 'n')
points(sndat[gaba == 0, -1], col = alpha('darkblue', 0.5), pch = 20, cex = 0.5)
points(sndat[gaba == 1, -1], col = alpha('red', 0.5), pch = 20, cex = 0.5)
abline(h = 0)
abline(v = 0)


points(colMeans(sndat[gaba == 0, -1])[1],colMeans(sndat[gaba == 0, -1])[2], col = 'blue', cex = 3)
points(colMeans(sndat[gaba == 0, -1])[1],colMeans(sndat[gaba == 0, -1])[2], col = 'blue', cex = 2, pch = 3)
points(colMeans(sndat[gaba == 1, -1])[1],colMeans(sndat[gaba == 1, -1])[2], col = 'red', cex = 3)
points(colMeans(sndat[gaba == 1, -1])[1],colMeans(sndat[gaba == 1, -1])[2], col = 'red', cex = 2, pch = 3)


A <- cov(sndat[gaba == 0, -1])
B <- cov(sndat[gaba == 1, -1])

ctrA <- colMeans(sndat[gaba == 0, -1])
RRA <- chol(A)

angles <- seq(0, 2*pi, length.out=200)          # angles for ellAipse
ellA    <- 1 * cbind(cos(angles), sin(angles)) %*% RRA  # ellAipse scaled with factor 1
ellACtr <- sweep(ellA, 2, ctrA, "+")               # center ellAipse to the data centroid
#plot(ellACtr, type="l", lwd=2, asp=1)            # plot ellAipse
#points(ctrA[1], ctrA[2], pch=4, lwd=2)            # plot data centroid
ellipse(ctrA, shape=A, radius=1, col=alpha("blue", 0.5), lty=2, add = TRUE, center.pch = 3)
ellipse(ctrA, shape=A, radius=2, col=alpha("blue", 0.5), lty=2, add = TRUE, center.pch = 0)
ellipse(ctrA, shape=A, radius=3, col=alpha("blue", 0.5), lty=2, add = TRUE, center.pch = 0)


ctrB <- colMeans(sndat[gaba == 1, -1])
RRB <- chol(B)


ellB    <- 1 * cbind(cos(angles), sin(angles)) %*% RRB  # ellBipse scaled with factor 1
ellBCtr <- sweep(ellB, 2, ctrB, "+")               # center ellBipse to the data centroid

ellipse(ctrB, shape=B, radius=1, col=alpha("red",0.5), lty=2, add = TRUE, center.pch = 3)
ellipse(ctrB, shape=B, radius=2, col=alpha("red",0.5), lty=2, add = TRUE, center.pch = 0)
ellipse(ctrB, shape=B, radius=3, col=alpha("red",0.5), lty=2, add = TRUE, center.pch = 0)

# Restricting hGMM to $K = 2$

We are comparing the cluster results to the `gaba` labels.

TN <- t1[1]

FN <- t1[3]

Pos <- TP + FN
Neg <- TN + FP
 
sens <- (TP/Pos)
spec <- TN/Neg
prec <- TP / (TP + FP)
recall <- TP / (TP + FN)

F1 <- 2 * prec*recall / (prec + recall)

ACC <- (TP + TN)/(TP + FP + FN + TN)
mis <- (FP + FN)/(TP + FP + FN + TN)
t1
```

# Permutation test for ARI

```{r perm}
p0 <- mclust::adjustedRandIndex(pred, gaba)
perms <- foreach(i = 1:1.5e4, .combine = c) %dopar% {
  set.seed(i*2)
  mclust::adjustedRandIndex(sample(pred), gaba)
}
pv0 <- sum(c(perms,p0) >= p0)/length(perms)
```


```{r hist, fig.height = 4, fig.width = 8}
hist(perms, xlim = c(min(perms), p0 + 0.25*p0),
     main = "permutation test of ARI values", probability = TRUE)
#hist(perms, probability = TRUE)
abline(v = p0, col = 'red')
t1
```

a <- function(x){
   w <- "[%d_%d_%d]" 
   b <- rep(w, x - 1)
   out <- paste0("[", paste0(b, collapse = "", sep = "_"), w, "]")
   return(out)
}

locPrint <- function(x){
  w <- "[%d_%d_%d]" 
  l <- c(list(w),x)
  do.call(sprintf,l)
}

boundingPoints <- foreach(i = 1:nrow(loc)) %do% {
  tmp <- c(
		lapply(-5:5, function(x) loc[i,] + c(-5,-5,x)),
		lapply(-5:5, function(x) loc[i,] + c(-5,0,x)),
		lapply(-5:5, function(x) loc[i,] + c(-5,6,x)),
    lapply(-5:5, function(x) loc[i,] + c(0,-5,x)),
		lapply(-5:5, function(x) loc[i,] + c(0,6,x)),
    lapply(-5:5, function(x) loc[i,] + c(6,-5,x)),
		lapply(-5:5, function(x) loc[i,] + c(6,0,x)),
		lapply(-5:5, function(x) loc[i,] + c(6,6,x))
    )

  xyz <- lapply(tmp, locPrint)
  paste0("[", paste0(xyz[1:(length(xyz)-1)], sep = "_", collapse= ""),
    xyz[length(xyz)],"]")
}

foreach(i = 1:dim(loc)[1]) %do% {
